                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Subscription&#44; &#40;Postage Prepaid.&#41;<lb/>
                &#36;2.00 per annum &#45; &#45; for the U. S.<lb/>
                &#36;2.50 &#34; &#45; &#45; &#45; for Europe<lb/></p>
            <p>The MENORAH&#44;<lb/>
                A Monthly Magazine<lb/>
                of Hebrew Literature&#44; Science and Art.<lb/></p>
            <p>Benjamin F. Peixotto&#44; Editor.<lb/>
                39 Broadway&#44; Rooms 18 &#38; 19.<lb/>
                5647<lb/>
                New York&#44; Aug 4 1887<lb/></p>
            <p>Rev &#38; dear friend&#44;<lb/></p>
            <p>I have mailed you a<lb/> special copy of the August Menorah<lb/> thinking as in Dr Felsenthal&#39;s<lb/> paper something interesting is given<lb/> from your pen&#44; you might wish to<lb/> have an extra copy.<lb/></p>
            <p>I say &#34;extra&#34; because the<lb/> copy regularly mailed to your talented<lb/> son Henry&#44; I felt sure w<hi rend="sup">d</hi> be seen<lb/> by you and hence have not mailed<lb/> a <sic>seperate</sic> number for yourself<lb/> but if you w<hi rend="sup">d</hi> like to have such in<lb/> future&#44; it will give me pleasure<lb/> to forward such.<lb/></p>
            <p>And now my dear<lb/> Dr. may I not crave something from<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>your erudite and charming pen for<lb/> the &#34;MenorahË¶ and will you not<lb/> contribute a paper for the October<lb/> No&#63;  I am most anxious to have<lb/> something on Spanish&#45;Jewish<lb/> literature or Italian and who<lb/> so powerfully &#34;clad and equipped&#34;<lb/> for such work.<lb/></p>
            <p>You doubtless have observed<lb/> how I am struggling to make the Menorah<lb/> a means and a medium for the<lb/> cultivation of a pure and true<lb/> love of Judaism&#44; of trying to reach<lb/> the young men and women of Israel&#44;<lb/> and of reviving the former spirit<lb/> of even the old.<lb/></p>
            <p>It is a hard task&#44; but I have<lb/> faith and courage and with the<lb/> co&#45;operation of the good and able<lb/> men and scholars of Israel.  I feel<lb/> I shall eventually succeed.<lb/></p>
            <p>Trusting to soon remember<lb/> you among my contributors<lb/> I am dear Dr.<lb/> very faithfully<lb/> yr friend<lb/> Benjamin F. Peixotto<lb/></p>
            <p>Dr Sabato Morais<lb/> Phila.<lb/></p>
            </body>
    </text>
